!! TiddlyWiki Wikitext — LLM Cheatsheet

This is a condensed syntax reference designed to be included in LLM system prompts or tool context. It covers the most commonly needed wikitext constructs with correct syntax and common mistakes to avoid.

!! Key Differences from Markdown

TiddlyWiki wikitext is ''not'' Markdown. These are the most common mistakes LLMs make:

|!Want |!Wrong (Markdown) |!Correct (Wikitext) |h
|Bold |`**bold**` |`''bold''` (two single-quotes) |
|Italic |`*italic*` |`//italic//` |
|Strikethrough |`~~text~~` |`~~text~~` (same!) |
|Link |`[text](url)` |`[[text|url]]` |
|External link |`[text](https://...)` |`[ext[text|https://...]]` |
|Image |`![alt](src)` |`[img[alt|src]]` |
|Heading |`# Heading` |`! Heading` |
|Bullet list |`- item` |`* item` |
|Numbered list |`1. item` |`# item` |
|Code inline |`` `code` `` |`` `code` `` (same!) |
|Code block |triple-backtick fencing |triple-backtick fencing (same!) |
|Horizontal rule |`---` |`---` (same!) |

!! Pragmas (top of tiddler only)

Pragmas must appear at the very start of the tiddler, before any content.

```
\procedure name(param1, param2:"default")
body text with <<param1>> references
\end

\function .myfilter(x) [<x>addprefix[hello ]]

\widget $my.widget(content)
<div class="wrapper"><<content>></div>
\end

\import [[$:/core/ui/PageMacros]]
\parameters(title:"Default", color:"blue")
\whitespace trim
\parsermode inline
\rules except wikilink
```

IMPORTANT: Use `\procedure` not `\define`. `\define` is deprecated.

!! Text Formatting

```
''bold''                  → <strong>
//italic//                → <em>
~~strikethrough~~         → <s>
^^superscript^^           → <sup>
,,subscript,,             → <sub>
__underscore__            → <u>
@@color:red;styled@@      → <span style="color:red;">
@@.myclass content@@      → <span class="myclass">
```

!! Links

```
[[Tiddler Title]]                   internal link
[[Display Text|Tiddler Title]]      internal link with label
[ext[https://example.com]]          external link
[ext[Click here|https://example.com]]  external link with label
[img[tooltip|image-source]]         image
[img width=200 [image-source]]      image with attributes
CamelCaseWords                      auto-link (suppress with ~CamelCase)
$:/system/tiddler                   auto-link to system tiddler
```

!! Headings

```
! Heading 1
!! Heading 2
!!! Heading 3
!!!! Heading 4
!!!!! Heading 5
!!!!!! Heading 6
!.css-class Heading with class
```

!! Lists

```
* Bullet item
** Nested bullet
# Numbered item
## Nested numbered
#* Mixed nesting (numbered > bullet)
; Definition term
: Definition description
> Blockquote line
```

!! Tables

```
|!Header 1|!Header 2|h
|Cell A1|Cell A2|
|Cell B1|Cell B2|
|Footer|Footer|f
|Caption text|c
|table-class|k
```

Alignment: `| left|`, `|right |`, `| center |`. Header cells use `!` after `|`.

!! Code

Inline code uses single or double backticks: <code>&#96;code&#96;</code> or <code>&#96;&#96;code with &#96; inside&#96;&#96;</code>.

Block code uses triple-backtick fencing with an optional language identifier on the opening line. The closing triple-backtick must be on its own line. Content inside is not parsed as wikitext.

!! Transclusion

```
{{tiddler-title}}                   include tiddler content
{{tiddler!!field}}                  include a field value
{{tiddler##index}}                  include a data index
{{tiddler||template}}               render through a template
{{{[tag[docs]]}}}                   filtered transclusion
{{{[tag[docs]]||template}}}         filtered with template
```

!! Macro/Procedure Calls

```
<<myproc>>                          no parameters
<<myproc "value 1" param2:value2>>  positional and named params
<<myproc param:"quoted value">>     old-style named (colon syntax)
<<myproc param:[[bracket value]]>>  old-style bracket-quoted
<<myproc param="text">>             new-style named (= syntax)
<<myproc param=<<var>>>>            variable value
<<myproc param={{tid!!field}}>>     indirect value
<<myproc param={{{[filter]}}}>>     filtered value
```

!! Variable/Filter Display

```
((variable-name))                   display variable value
(((filter-expression)))             display filter result
((variable||, ))                    with custom separator
```

!! Widgets (HTML-like)

```
<$list filter="[tag[doc]]" variable="item">
  <<item>>
</$list>

<$set name="myvar" value="hello">
  <<myvar>>
</$set>

<$text text="literal text"/>

<$reveal type="match" state="$:/state/show" text="yes">
  Revealed content
</$reveal>
```

!!! Attribute Value Forms (7 types)

```
attr="string value"                 string (also: 'single' [[bracket]] """triple""")
attr={{{[filter]}}}                 filtered (runtime)
attr={{tiddler!!field}}             indirect (runtime lookup)
attr=<<variable>>                   variable/macro
attr=((varname))                    MVV reference
attr=`text with $(var)$ subst`      substituted
attr                                boolean (true)
```

!! Conditionals

```
<%if [<myVar>match[yes]]%>
Shown when true.
<%elseif [<myVar>match[maybe]]%>
Alternative.
<%else%>
Fallback.
<%endif%>
```

!! Filter Expressions (mini-language)

Filters appear inside `{{{ }}}`, widget attributes, and `\import`.

```
[tag[docs]]                         tiddlers tagged "docs"
[tag[docs]sort[title]]              chained operators
[tag[docs]] [tag[help]]             union (OR)
[tag[docs]] +[sort[title]]          pipe through (AND)
[tag[docs]] -[tag[draft]]           except
[tag[docs]] ~[[FallbackTiddler]]    else (if previous empty)
[tag[docs]] :filter[get[text]length[]compare:number:gt[100]]
                                    named run prefix
```

!!! Operator syntax

```
[operator[literal]]                 literal parameter
[operator{tiddler!!field}]          indirect parameter
[operator<variable>]                variable parameter
[!operator[literal]]                negated
[operator:suffix[literal]]          with suffix
```

!! Quote Block

```
<<<
Quoted text here.
<<<

<<<.citation
With a class.
<<< Attribution
```

!! Style Block

```
@@background-color:#ffd;color:#333;
Styled paragraph.
@@

@@.warning
Paragraph with CSS class.
@@
```

!! Typed Block

```
$$$text/html
<b>Raw HTML</b>
$$$

$$$.svg
<svg>...</svg>
$$$
```

!! Hard Line Breaks

```
"""
Line one
Line two
Line three
"""
```

Each newline becomes `<br>`.

!! Comments

```
<!-- This comment is not rendered -->
```

!! Common Patterns

!!! Conditional class on a widget

```
<div class={{{ [{!!status}match[active]then[highlight]] }}}>
```

!!! List with template

```
<$list filter="[tag[task]!has[done]]" template="TaskTemplate"/>
```

!!! Transclude with parameters

```
{{MyTemplate||$:/templates/card|param1|param2}}
```

!!! Setting and using a variable

```
<$let greeting="Hello" name=<<currentTiddler>>>
  <<greeting>>, <<name>>!
</$let>
```

!! Things to Never Do

* For new code, never use `\define` — use `\procedure` instead
* Never use Markdown syntax (`**bold**`, `[text](url)`, `# heading`) — it will not work
* Never use `<script>` tags — use widgets instead
* Never assume HTML entities work everywhere — use `&amp;` `&lt;` `&gt;` only where needed
* Never put block-level content on the same line as an opening widget tag — use a blank line after `>`
* Never use `\whitespace trim` for content — only for code or templates
* In `\whitespace trim` templates, use `<$text text=" "/>` for explicit spaces, or use the built-in gap classes:
** `tc-tiny-gap` / `tc-tiny-gap-left` / `tc-tiny-gap-right` — 0.25em
** `tc-small-gap` / `tc-small-gap-left` / `tc-small-gap-right` — 0.5em
** `tc-big-gap` / `tc-big-gap-left` / `tc-big-gap-right` — 1em
** Example: `<span class="tc-small-gap-right"/>` inserts a 0.5em right margin